The paper discusses the application of first-order probabilistic methods in reasoning about concepts not contained in the probabilistic knowledge base. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also proposes the use of taxonomic knowledge to impose structure onto possible worlds, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the representation of probability distributions, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses reasoning systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
